I get why it played out that way.
And I think it probably really benefited the apprentice.
Yet it comes back to the initial question for me.
Should he have got that thing to 90 degrees?
The original poster?
Are you cool with 89.8 when it comes to a piece of conduit running in some supply closet?
That's a good question.
I think if it's my house, 89.8 is just fine.
If you did the work.
If I did the work.
Yeah.
If it's somebody else's house and I did the work, it's got to be 90.
Well, I'd give him even more.
I'd give him 91.
